          Passionate educators committed to nurturing every child's potential through nature-based learning.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Mr Jackson - Featured -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-3xl p-8 lg:p-12 shadow-lg mb-12 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 items-center">
          <div class="mx-auto">
            <div class="relative w-48 h-48 lg:w-56 lg:h-56">
              <img
                src="/images/team/matthew-jackson.avif"
                alt="Mr Jackson"
                class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-full border-4 border-[#c9a962]/30 shadow-xl"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-2 text-center md:text-left">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-2 bg-[#c9a962]/20 rounded-full text-[#c9a962] text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Head Teacher</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-[#1e3d29] mb-4">Mr Jackson</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Mr Jackson has a true passion for learning and a firm belief in the power of outdoor education. With over 15 years of experience in international schools, he champions a learning approach that gives children the freedom to explore, ask questions, and grow in resilience.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
              Beyond his academic qualifications, including an MA in Political History from the University of London, Mr Jackson has helped establish educational charitable projects in Europe, Asia and East Africa. You'll find him greeting Forest students with a warm smile each morning, ready to inspire them for a day of adventure and discovery.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

